Thousands of South Korean police stormed a religious compound today as they searched for a fugitive businessman wanted in connection with April's ferry disaster.

Donning riot gear, officers forced their way into the sprawling church and complex in Anseong, 50 miles south of Seoul, at around 8am (12am GMT).

They were hunting billionaire Yoo Byung-eun, who is believed to own the vessel that sank, leaving more than 300 people dead or missing.

